OL,3,CHuw Edwards 'snubbed rival' David
OL,4,CDimbleby during lunch, says ex-No 10
OL,5,Caide
OL,7,F"The big lesson is to not put someone
OL,8,Fon such a pedestal where we don't
OL,9,Fquestion the possibility that they
OL,10,Fhave failings.
OL,12,F"We can't take away from the fact that
OL,13,FHuw was hugely successful with a
OL,14,Ftremendous ability as a broadcaster,
OL,15,Fbut there's now a dark shadow over all
OL,16,Fof that. In the end he will be
OL,17,Fremembered as someone who did
OL,18,Fsomething awful."
